Kratom is also found to have properties for opiate addiction. As the plant has cross-tolerance with opiates, it's employed for opiate detox treatment especially in New Zealand. For around 6 weeks, patients are let to smoke kratom when opiate withdrawal symptoms occur. Inside the time range, the kratom dosage will be gradually reduced. Therapeutic utilisation of the plant should be controlled by authorized party as regular use of kratom alone can cause addiction although not as severe as opium or heroin addictions. In fact, in some countries such as Australia, Malaysia, Thailand, New Zealand, Denmark, and Myanmar using kratom is controlled and illegal possession of the herb can result in strict penalty.

More studies on kratom also revealed that the herb contains antioxidants and for that reason is considered to have essential benefits similar to those present in Green tea extract. The herb can also be found to contain fiber which is useful when you are relieving constipation.